Meeting Minutes

Date
Not specified

Attendees
Project team
Client

Purpose
Review current progress of the application
Prepare for User Acceptance Testing (UAT)
Collect feedback and define remaining tasks before Monday deadline

Key Updates

Progress

* Application reached a functional stage
* Core features implemented and working locally
* User testing conducted with two initial users
* Additional testing planned with medical students

User Testing

* Initial testers were non-medical users
* Feedback focused on usability and clarity
* Key issues identified:

  * Confusing graphs
  * Lack of explanations
  * Cluttered layout
* UI updated:

  * Graphs placed side by side
  * Dynamic graph added for patient inputs

UAT Plan

* UAT scheduled for Monday
* Purpose: final user sign-off
* Client will test the software and provide feedback
* Team aims to complete refinements before UAT

Technical Notes

Deployment

* Current version not yet published
* Frequent updates delayed deployment
* Plan to publish latest version after meeting

Performance

* API issues identified due to multiple simultaneous requests
* Temporary delay added between requests to prevent crashes

AI Functionality

* AI currently restricted to 3 treatment options

  * Statins
  * Blood pressure treatment
  * One additional intervention
* Restriction added to avoid unsafe medical advice
* Potential to expand AI scope discussed but not prioritized

Data and Model Issues

* Bayesian model influenced heavily by “blocked vessels” variable
* Discrepancy between AI output and model output observed
* Dataset imbalance noted
* Need to refine:

  * Model weighting
  * AI prompt logic
  * Threshold for “significant difference” between outputs

UI and UX Feedback

Clarity

* Graphs require clear explanations
* Terms like “clinical contribution” unclear
* Users need guidance on what each section shows

Input Requirements

* All fields must be filled before analysis
* Instruction to users needs to be added

Risk Output

* Confusion around percentages and medical meaning
* Need clearer explanation of:

  * Risk calculation
  * Accuracy metrics

PDF Export

* Feature implemented
* Formatting issues need fixing

Open Issues

* Improve explanation for all graphs and outputs
* Refine AI prompt to reduce over-reliance on blocked vessels
* Define threshold for model vs AI discrepancy
* Validate medical assumptions with reliable sources
* Improve PDF layout
* Add user instructions for input completion
* Explain accuracy calculation (MSE or equivalent)
* Finalize comprehensive test cases after user testing

Next Steps

Before Monday

* Publish latest version
* Complete remaining user testing
* Implement UI explanations
* Refine AI logic and prompts
* Fix PDF export issues

Monday

* Conduct UAT with client
* Gather final feedback
* Complete UAT documentation

Additional Notes

* App aims to show difference between:

  * Mathematical model (Bayesian network)
  * General AI estimation
* Dataset limitations acknowledged
* Further validation required for medical credibility
